TextBlock.TextLine: In Antwerp 5 gb 1681
London, John Loyd
th
S. my last to you was on the 22: passt. sence recd yd of ditto I dohere by
assure you againe that mr. suke norton, which went by the name of
m. more is Really dead & to the further satisfaction shall endeavour
to procure a notdriall attestation, of the time of his dead & what
elle might serve in occasion butt for that I want some dayes time
more, to have itt in forma this week hope to have a parcell of tykes
compleated, of which shall send you the perticuleirs p next with the
attestation if possible & so with kinde saents &mane
@ 5 ditto 1681
London mist scawen
th
S. in answer to yd of 14: past. hope you red. the tykes before this & that you
found them to content: I do much wonder that you wright of 6 greatlead
casleure you, you never made any mention that they aro not vendable
besides gnever send any packes to England, butt that there were andonghst
of them, as well as of the rest, besides Ihad send you a note before of the conte
returne you thanckes for accepting my bill if I had had the least thoughts
to disoblige you with my drawing, sure I should rather ½ have delayd itt
3 weekes & ashed leave before hand or exspected yd remised which att
any time hence forward shall be observe when the salempores are ready
please to send them forward as you shall iudge convement foo clave yett
some white of N.3: so you neednot to incommode you I hope to cleare
all before you come over & to have the acctt. ready then. Entrim
you should want any goods to putt in the salempores you may order m
maynard to provide the needfull, or elee as you jiudge courement Iwonder
that my packett of lace was not come to yd handes yett itt beeng onely
DN.3 for whoch I hope you will allow mee what is reasonable N.4 is still
with mee, because I do not finde you inclined to sell for my acctt butt if you
please to havs itt allowing provision onely ill send itt as itt cost mee here itt ecayns
theap as ever lacewas bought I am confident Ican serve you & comp. inthat
as wellkas munctuall, that noother shall out domce, of which shall shew you the
Effect when you be here intrim where in Iean serve you pray command mee
a 5 ditto 1681
that am with hinde saluts

geworde nu comen te beantwoorde de ul van 27 past 2 & 3 deser dernhoste

ul ordre de lertifiratie te senden, met de packen aen boort piudar beuseer
verlegen soo dat wenschte die voor alles comre geapiieert worden het
pack gearriveert met haulot son verwahte p wagen, als mede advies
vant geene weijders is voorgevallen waermede blijve 6 ditto 1681

Brussel in. Anthan Russeau
en suite de l'agreable ord. du 5 for. J'ay bien receu le pacquet contenant 3 pettit all'ordinaiy
qui tartinont d'scy pour nieuwporte demain advessee a m. Michil Vallego pour suivre vos ondres
Ils seront la dimanche au middy avecq le possillon, ceste voye est fort seeure car les mestagiers
de Brussel jusqu sey sont epemt de tous frais, & d'estre visite selon le l'octroy qu' les
ont obtenu dans le temps de areiducque albert & nos messagiers ne passent pas & G and,
tellement que lles ne sont pas cisite non plus, & quand ils vienint a Brugges, donnent les
pacquits ad Postillon de m. Ballego mesme, ce que vous serve d'advis. j'ay payes pour
les 3 pacquets ensemble 12 pastar de Brussel jusqu icy, & ma prouision 15 pattar & la piece
a vostre gad je laisseray mr. Vallege payer la port jusque la, qui saru leutant comme
de Brussel a tnieuupoite puis que je vous assere qu'en vous occasions je ne manquenay pas de
faire tous billigences a me. avantage
a6d
Brussel Juff. Anna Peeters
tot antw. aen den ul van gisteren dient als dat mijn sH. ul neve van d. Bernaerts hier is
gecomen, aen den welcken alles hebbe geseyt het gene redelijcq was, die daer op ul broeder hieft
1eers
gaen vinden, den welcken dan gistren naer middagh bij mij is gecomen, &wij hebben ont recq.
& alles esten geset, soo dat ick niet en twijffele, ofte ick sal in corte dagen den vrint in
Engelant contentet. gegeeven hebben., ul broeder vertreckt morgen naer d Hernaerts al waer wel
2 a 3 dagen sal blijve & dan weder t'huijs comen, soo ick van hem heb verstaen. nu versoecke ul
dat aen mij gelieft te laten weeten, ofte ul, ofte ul moeder erfg. is van m Jan Peetertsal
ul broeder, 't welck soo seynde, ul & mij behoorde te laten weeten, oft ul met d'afreckenne
door ul broeders gedaen, voor ul paert te vreden tijt, want alles dat ick doen, is niet alleen
om mijn consciente gerieft te stellen, maer om elck een het syne te geeven, & in ruste te leeven
soo sal ul antw verwaghten, &
de lakens gaen overmorgen naer eng. & het gelt
tot alles toe sal volgen, 't gene eerder soude geschiet hebben, waer 't saecken dat maer schriftelijck
ord. & quitantie hadde gehadt, Ick hebbe de oblig van den marcq. Conflans van ƒ 1250-
